ARRAYS:=a specialized object used to store an ordered collection of values

 ex:=const fruits = ["Apple", "Banana"];
  ARRAY METHODS:
  ---> Add/Remove Elements:
   .push(val): Adds to the end.
   .pop(): Removes from the end.
   .unshift(val): Adds to the beginning.
   .shift(): Removes from the beginning.
   .splice(index, count, ...items): Adds or removes items at a specific position.
  --> Searching and Iteration:
   .indexOf(val): Returns the first index of a value, or -1 if not found.
   .includes(val): Returns true if the array contains the value.
   .forEach(fn): Executes a function for every element.
   .map(fn): Creates a new array by transforming every element.
   .filter(fn): Creates a new array with elements that pass a test.
 
